iles.org/menu/library/treaties/non-proliferation-treaty/trty_npt_1970-03-05.htm NuclearFiles.org] Summary and text from the nuclear NPT\n* [http://disarmament.un.org/treaties/t/npt Membership/Signatories]\n* [http://www.npolicy.org/ The Nonproliferation Policy Education Center (NPEC)]- A not-for-profit organization based in Washington, D.C., and founded in 1994 to promote a better understanding of strategic weapons proliferation issues among policymakers, scholars and the media.\n* [http://alsos.wlu.edu/adv_rst.aspx?keyword=NPT&results=10 Annotated Bibliography on the NPT] from the [[Alsos Digital Library for Nuclear Issues]]\n* [http://newsblaze.com/story/20080630082120tsop.nb/topstory.html Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty Turns 40 Today in 2008], NewsBlaze\n* {{ill|George Perkovich|de}}, [https://web.archive.org/web/20111210090856/http://ifri.org/downloads/Perkovich_Reforming_Nuclear_Order.pdf \"Principles for Reforming the Nuclear Order\"], ''Proliferation Papers'', Paris, Ifri, Fall 2008.\n* [https://2001-2009.state.gov/t/isn/wmd/nnp/ Compilation of speeches and papers relevant to NPT Review Cycle], [[U.S. Department of State]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100119180036/http://dfa.gov.ph/main/index.php/newsroom/npt-information-a-updates The 2010 Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT) Review Conference], [[Department of Foreign Affairs, Republic of the Philippines]]\n* [http://alsos.wlu.edu/adv_rst.aspx?keyword=NPT&results=10 Annotated bibliography for the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty] from the Alsos Digital Library for Nuclear Issues\n* [[The American Academy of Arts and Sciences]] [https://web.archive.org/web/20120414221108/http://www.amacad.org/publications/nonproliferation.aspx Nuclear Collisions: Discord, Reform & the Nuclear Nonproliferation Regime]\n{{Cold War}}\n{{Nuclear weapons limitation treaty}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty}}\n[[Category:Arms control treaties]]\n[[Category:Non-proliferation treaties]